docker compose up --build

Ways to Force a New Image Every Time
1. Use --build option (most common)
docker compose up --build


Tells Compose: always rebuild before starting containers.

If you don’t use --build, it may reuse the existing image.

2. Use --force-recreate
docker compose up --build --force-recreate


Rebuilds the image and forces containers to be recreated, even if nothing changed.

3. Disable Cache During Build

If you want to ignore Docker’s build cache completely:

docker compose build --no-cache
docker compose up


or in one step:

docker compose up --build --force-recreate --no-deps --remove-orphans
